to deal with this?

00:43:42.480 --> 00:43:43.780
&gt;&gt; Sujatha Gidla: Yeah.

00:43:43.780 --> 00:43:45.210
I think India is
roiling, more roiling

00:43:45.210 --> 00:43:47.300
than outsiders will realize.

00:43:47.300 --> 00:43:54.080
There is ferment of the workers,
they're ferment of peasants,

00:43:54.080 --> 00:43:58.480
and the students are
really struggling

00:43:58.480 --> 00:44:01.030
under the current Modi regime.

00:44:01.030 --> 00:44:05.300
And India is producing
18 year olds,

00:44:05.300 --> 00:44:09.040
like 1 million every
month or year?

00:44:09.040 --> 00:44:10.810
One of those books
mentions that.

00:44:10.810 --> 00:44:15.910
So, there's going to be an
army of unemployed in India,

00:44:15.910 --> 00:44:22.280
and that makes it a, you know,
fertile ground for castes --

00:44:22.280 --> 00:44:26.940
caste based, you know, wars and
discrimination, and violence.

00:44:26.940 --> 00:44:31.170
And so, I don't think any
political party that wants

00:44:31.170 --> 00:44:33.540
to work within this structure,

00:44:33.540 --> 00:44:36.250
parliamentary structure
can bring down castes.

00:44:36.250 --> 00:44:39.700
And I think that the only way
is to bring down the structures.

00:44:39.700 --> 00:44:43.090
And it may seem impossible,
but you know,

00:44:43.090 --> 00:44:44.960
things happen like that.

00:44:44.960 --> 00:44:46.950
In the world it happened
like that,

00:44:46.950 --> 00:44:50.140
in America Civil War happened
and destroyed slavery.

00:44:50.140 --> 00:44:51.440
&gt;&gt; Rumaan Alma: Yeah.

00:44:51.440 --> 00:44:53.510
&gt;&gt; Sujatha Gidla: And in French
